===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|heahweg|hēahweġ|main road}}, corresponding to {{term|high}} + {{term|way}}:
* Old English {{term|heah|hēah|of great height, tall}}, from {{proto|Germanic|hauhaz}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|kowkos|hill}} +
* Old English {{term|weg|weġ|lang=ang|road, path}}, from {{proto|Germanic|wegaz}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|weǵʰ-|to move}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈhaɪweɪ/}}
* {{audio|en-us-highway.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|aɪweɪ}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A main, direct [[public]] [[road]], especially a multi-[[lane]], high speed [[thoroughfare]] connecting major population centers.
# {{rail}} Any public road for [[vehicular]] traffic.

